The Hokkaido Bank Ltd is issuing a 30 mlndlr convertible eurobond due March 31, 2002 with an indicated2-1/4 pct coupon and priced at par, lead manager NomuraInternational Ltd said.    Terms will be fixed on March 10, involving a premium ofabout five pct above a six-day average. The conversion periodwill run from April 20, 1987 to March 20, 2002.    The bonds will be sold in denominations of 5,000 dlrs andwill be listed in Luxembourg. Total fees of 2-1/2 pct includeone pct for management and underwriting and 1-1/2 pct forselling, including an 20 basis point praecipuum.    Nomura said the bonds are callable from March 31, 1990 at104, declining by 1/2 pct per annum.    There will be no calls before March 31, 1992 unless theshare price reaches at least 150 pct of the conversion price. REUTER&#3;